---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Wiki" description="Groundwork local project notes">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Wiki</h1>
        <p>Local project notes capture durable decisions from building Groundwork. They are review context, not package API documentation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-grid">
        <article class="gw-card gw-stack">
          <p class="gw-caption">Documentation practice</p>
          <h2 class="gw-heading-m"><a class="gw-link" href="/wiki/flows-as-human-testable-documentation/">Flows as human-testable documentation</a></h2>
          <p class="gw-body--sm">Why Groundwork documents full interactive journeys as well as isolated components.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="gw-card gw-stack">
          <p class="gw-caption">Review workflow</p>
          <h2 class="gw-heading-m"><a class="gw-link" href="/wiki/ui-review-workflow/">UI review workflow</a></h2>
          <p class="gw-body--sm">How the local UI review script supports human inspection and layout diagnostics.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
